			<ns0:name>kschi...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108470876877739532758/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Note that the main issue is that most instructions can infer their type from an argument. For binary (arithmetic) operators in pnacl-llc, less than 0.01% of the instructions can't infer the type from the argument (because the argument is a forward reference). A simple solution to this is to introduce "Type" forward references that will apply to the next instruction.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-06-20T19:58:42.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-06-20T19:58:42.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 3 by kschi...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3507#c3" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3507/comments/full/3" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>